Yall ever have that anxiety that you feel will go away with using? Then you use, the anxiety is just as strong or worse but there's a weird level of comfort in it? I keep coming back to different pills after time away thinking it'll make me feel nice for a bit and not stress but I always end up with the same outcome; More anxiety, shame, and a feeling like maybe I just didn't do enough to drown it out. I'm finding it hard to combat that urge to fall deep into use again and go completely numb. I've been 5 years clean from H but have been having some of the worst cravings since quitting. Any advice? I'm trying to keep busy and fill my time with family and work but I'm finding it harder and harder to say no to a night of nodding ya know?

The only way I ever maintained any length of clean time was finding a hobby I absolutely love‚Ä¶ hula hooping. And it‚Äôs such a good emotional release. I had been on methadone 3 diff times I started using months after I turned 16 and got off methadone the last time when I turned 26 and as soon as I felt better I pick up a hoop and didn‚Äôt put it down. It‚Äôs no wonder I relapsed when I had to get foot surgery that rendered me unable to hoop for 4 months which coincided with right when COVID started I healed March 9 2020 and it‚Äôs been a struggle since cause I can‚Äôt hoop a lot do to my health issues. 

Find a hobby that‚Äôs affordable and that you can do at home or close by. Something that wouldn‚Äôt require you to travel crazy far cause I swear I was in my hoops at least 5 days a week for a good couple years happiest time of my life
I was just thinking of looking into one

Also you do not want to have to go through wd again I promise you I did it last July and this one and caved again it‚Äôs no fun. I know it sounds fun when it‚Äôs been years but it‚Äôs an extremely slippery slope which I know you know. One night turns into the weekends turns into once a week and the weekends and bam all day everyday back on it. I hope this helps. Also 5 years is amazing congrats that‚Äôs very impressive. I thought after 3 years I could do it one night and now it‚Äôs been 4 years of struggling again.
